Excelent', "Hooves.\xa0 Beating.\xa0 Pounding their way across the earth.\xa0 No stopping.\xa0 Making time.\xa0 Keeping stride with the tick tock of the earth's clock.\xa0 The howling cloak\xa0of darkness.\xa0 Following.\xa0 Emitting from within.\xa0 Each step scarring the ground once more.\xa0 Bringing death's rider closer to settle the score.\xa0 You can hear the gallop of time ticking against you.\xa0 Like a fog that settles in without a sound.\xa0 Surrounding.\xa0 Leaving no escape.\xa0 But now you listen.\xa0 Like a knight on guard, weary in your iron clad boots.\xa0 Walk briskly.\xa0 Lightly.\xa0 Don't alert the hooves silently stalking though the woods.\xa0 Pause. . . Listen. . .\xa0 Silence is your hidden ally.\xa0 The leaves narrate your escape.\xa0 Led on by the whispers of the wind.\xa0 Breath carefully.\xa0 The fog will find you if you give it time.\xa0 Press on.\xa0 The trees have become your labyrinth.\xa0 A misplaced footstep upon a condemning twig.\xa0 FREEZE. . . Listen to the night.\xa0 Search the chords of chilling air. . . A faint clap.\xa0 The hollow sound echoing through the dark, followed by the tendrils of a breathless fog.\xa0 You must go!\xa0 RUN!\xa0 Command your legs through the deadfall!\xa0 Move your arms in harmony with your calves!\xa0 Be a conditioned tactician!\xa0 A clap. . . Then another!\xa0 No longer faint but a rhythmic thump.\xa0 You plot your course.\xa0 The terrain is your chess board.\xa0 Your movement is quick.\xa0 Disheveling fear with each step.\xa0 But the horse replants it four steps at a time.\xa0 Gaining position with red furnaces guiding its eyes.\xa0 You make a blind move.\xa0 Your armor snagging on a limb!\xa0 The spill sends you crashing down.\xa0 Spiraling into the earth as you try to stay above.\xa0 Silence.\xa0 Your only ally, now against you.\xa0 The fog lists in.\xa0 Filling the voids between you and your trees.\xa0 You can't move, don't dare to move, but you must.\xa0 You lift your head.\xa0 Open your eyes.\xa0 The ghastly white fog has socked you in the course.\xa0 A figure.\xa0 So consuming and dark.\xa0 His approach.\xa0 No more moves.\xa0 He has taken you with his horse.", "\xa0\xa0 -The Grim Reaper's Horse", 'I was just going to favorite one, but my favorite color is green.... ", 'Overall, I love this piece, this is something that i could write a story based on just this one scene in this picture.
